article.headline: Old Dominion 75, Drexel 71
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Gerald Lee hit two free throws with 11 seconds left to seal the victory as Old Dominion beat Drexel 75-71 in double overtime Thursday night. Lee finished with 23 points. His free throw with 4:30 left in the second overtime gave Old Dominion the lead for good at 61-60. Drexel battled back after Old Dominion built its lead to six points, cutting the margin to two points with 12 seconds left. Old Dominion held a 15-point lead with 12:45 remaining in regulation but Drexel put together a 20-4 run that gave the Dragons the lead at 49-48 with 3:17 left. Brandon Johnson hit a 3-pointer with 0.8 second left in regulation to tie the score at 54-54 and send the game into overtime. In the first overtime, Drexel led 59-60 with 1:01 remaining but a free throw by Lee tied the score 60-60 and forced the second overtime. Johnson finished with seven points and five steals. Frank Hassell and Brian Henderson each scored 10 points for Old Dominion (13-13, 8-6 Colonial Athletic Association). Tramayne Hawthorne led Drexel (10-16, 3-11 CAA) with 21 points. Scott Rodgers added 13 points and Frank Elegar scored 12 points.
